      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, can u look at these logs? we're seeing some weird p99 spikes in the payment-gateway microservice. nothing constant, just intermittent hits during high traffic. \n\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:22:01.452Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 450, \"db_connection_pool\": {\"active\": 48, \"idle\": 2}, \"request_id\": \"req-9928-ax\"}\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:22:01.488Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 12, \"db_connection_pool\": {\"active\": 12, \"idle\": 38}, \"request_id\": \"req-9929-bz\"}\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:22:02.101Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 890, \"db_connection_pool\": {\"active\": 50, \"idle\": 0}, \"request_id\": \"req-9930-cq\"}\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:22:02.115Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 15, \"db_connection_pool\": {\"active\": 10, \"idle\": 40}, \"request_id\": \"req-9931-dr\"}\n\nseems like the pool might be hitting limits when things ramp up. any ideas?",
